The paper deals with algorithms for computing weak visibility polygons in simple polygons, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm presented in the paper involves preprocessing and data structures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions time and space complexity, which are topics covered in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem of weak visibility polygons can also be related to graph theory, which falls under cs.GR (Graph Theory). Finally, the paper mentions an output-sensitive algorithm, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
